sudo cat /etc/passwd
or
cd /home and then ls

the above shows all the users 


To make a new group of users-

-sudo groupadd Devops
this will create a group with name Devops
to view all groups - 
-sudo cat /etc/group

we can create users with useradd -m jetha and babita and add it to tapusena
to add, we can 
-sudo gpasswd -a jetha tapusena
to add multiple users,
-sudo gpasswd -m jetha,babita tapusena

to give permissions of a file to group - 
-sudo chgrp tapusena file1.txt


https://www.redswitches.com/blog/add-user-to-group-linux/#what-is-a-group-in-linux

